<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>BoxLang Charts - Responsive Features</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background: ##f5f7fa;
        }
        .header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, ##667eea 0%, ##764ba2 100%);
            padding: 40px 20px;
            margin: -20px -20px 30px -20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .header h1 {
            margin: 0 0 10px 0;
            font-size: 2.5em;
        }
        .header p {
            margin: 0;
            opacity: 0.9;
            font-size: 1.1em;
        }
        .chart-section {
            background: white;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            max-width: 900px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        .chart-title {
            font-size: 1.5em;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: ##667eea;
        }
        .chart-description { font-size: 14px; color: ##666; margin-bottom: 15px; }
        .chart-container { margin: 10px 0; }
        .responsive-container { width: 100%; max-width: 800px; padding: 10px; background: ##f9f9f9; border: 2px dashed ##ddd; }
        .feature-highlight { background: ##e8f4f8; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid ##3498db; margin: 10px 0; }
        .back-link {
            display: inline-block;
            background: ##667eea;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 25px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: block;
            width: fit-content;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .back-link:hover {
            background: ##764ba2;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>üì± BoxLang Charts - Responsive Features</h1>
        <p>Resize your browser window to see responsive charts in action!</p>
    </div>

    <a href="index.bxm" class="back-link">‚Üê Back to Test Suite</a>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">1. Fully Responsive Chart (Default Behavior)</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart will resize to fit its container while maintaining aspect ratio.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true" (default), maintainAspectRatio="true" (default)
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Responsive Pie Chart"
                     chartwidth="600" chartheight="300"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="true">
                <bx:chartseries type="pie" colorlist="FF6384,36A2EB,FFCE56,4BC0C0"
                               serieslabel="Market Share">
                    <bx:chartdata item="Product A" value="150" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Product B" value="200" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Product C" value="100" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Product D" value="75" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">2. Responsive Chart with Custom Aspect Ratio</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart uses a custom aspect ratio of 3 (wider than default).</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true", maintainAspectRatio="true", aspectRatio="3"
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Wide Format Bar Chart"
                     chartwidth="800" chartheight="300"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="true"
                     aspectRatio="3"
                     xaxistitle="Categories" yaxistitle="Values"
                     showygridlines="true">
                <bx:chartseries type="bar" colorlist="131cd7,ED2939,4BC0C0,d47f00"
                               serieslabel="Performance Metrics">
                    <bx:chartdata item="Q1" value="150" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Q2" value="200" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Q3" value="175" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Q4" value="225" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">3. Responsive Chart Without Aspect Ratio Constraint</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart fills its container's height without maintaining aspect ratio.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true", maintainAspectRatio="false"
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container" style="height: 400px;">
            <bx:chart title="Flexible Height Line Chart"
                     chartwidth="600" chartheight="400"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="false"
                     xaxistitle="Time" yaxistitle="Value"
                     showxgridlines="true" showygridlines="true">
                <bx:chartseries type="line" colorlist="36A2EB"
                               serieslabel="Trend Data">
                    <bx:chartdata item="Jan" value="100" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Feb" value="150" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Mar" value="130" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Apr" value="180" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="May" value="200" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Jun" value="175" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">4. Non-Responsive Fixed-Size Chart</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart maintains a fixed size regardless of container width.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="false"
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Fixed Size Doughnut Chart"
                     chartwidth="400" chartheight="400"
                     responsive="false"
                     showlegend="true">
                <bx:chartseries type="doughnut" colorlist="FF6384,36A2EB,FFCE56"
                               serieslabel="Distribution">
                    <bx:chartdata item="Category A" value="300" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Category B" value="200" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Category C" value="100" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">5. Responsive Area Chart with Square Aspect Ratio</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart uses an aspect ratio of 1 for a square layout.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true", maintainAspectRatio="true", aspectRatio="1"
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Square Area Chart"
                     chartwidth="500" chartheight="500"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="true"
                     aspectRatio="1"
                     xaxistitle="Period" yaxistitle="Usage"
                     showxgridlines="true" showygridlines="true">
                <bx:chartseries type="area" colorlist="9966FF"
                               serieslabel="Resource Usage">
                    <bx:chartdata item="00:00" value="45" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="04:00" value="30" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="08:00" value="75" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="12:00" value="90" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="16:00" value="80" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="20:00" value="60" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">6. Responsive Horizontal Bar Chart</div>
        <div class="chart-description">Horizontal bar charts work great with responsive sizing.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true", maintainAspectRatio="true", aspectRatio="1.5"
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Resource Utilization"
                     chartwidth="600" chartheight="400"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="true"
                     aspectRatio="1.5"
                     xaxistitle="Percentage" yaxistitle="Resources">
                <bx:chartseries type="horizontalbar" colorlist="FF6384,36A2EB,FFCE56,4BC0C0"
                               serieslabel="Current Usage">
                    <bx:chartdata item="CPU" value="75" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Memory" value="60" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Disk" value="45" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Network" value="30" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">7. Side-by-Side Responsive Charts</div>
        <div class="chart-description">Multiple responsive charts in a flex layout.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Layout:</strong> Two charts side-by-side, each taking 50% width
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
                <bx:chart title="Chart 1"
                         chartwidth="400" chartheight="300"
                         responsive="true"
                         maintainAspectRatio="true">
                    <bx:chartseries type="pie" colorlist="FF6384,36A2EB,FFCE56">
                        <bx:chartdata item="A" value="100" />
                        <bx:chartdata item="B" value="150" />
                        <bx:chartdata item="C" value="75" />
                    </bx:chartseries>
                </bx:chart>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
                <bx:chart title="Chart 2"
                         chartwidth="400" chartheight="300"
                         responsive="true"
                         maintainAspectRatio="true">
                    <bx:chartseries type="bar" colorlist="4BC0C0,9966FF,FF9F40">
                        <bx:chartdata item="X" value="120" />
                        <bx:chartdata item="Y" value="90" />
                        <bx:chartdata item="Z" value="160" />
                    </bx:chartseries>
                </bx:chart>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">8. Responsive Chart with Resize Delay (Performance Optimization)</div>
        <div class="chart-description">This chart uses resizeDelay to debounce resize events for better performance.</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Attributes:</strong> responsive="true", resizeDelay="100" (100ms debounce)
        </div>
        <div class="responsive-container">
            <bx:chart title="Optimized Responsive Chart"
                     chartwidth="600" chartheight="300"
                     responsive="true"
                     maintainAspectRatio="true"
                     resizeDelay="100">
                <bx:chartseries type="bar" colorlist="FF6384,36A2EB,FFCE56,4BC0C0"
                               serieslabel="Performance Data">
                    <bx:chartdata item="Jan" value="120" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Feb" value="150" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Mar" value="135" />
                    <bx:chartdata item="Apr" value="180" />
                </bx:chartseries>
            </bx:chart>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="chart-section">
        <div class="chart-title">Implementation Notes</div>
        <div class="feature-highlight">
            <strong>Key Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>responsive</strong> - When true, chart resizes to fit container (default: true)</li>
                <li><strong>maintainAspectRatio</strong> - When true, maintains width/height ratio during resize (default: true)</li>
                <li><strong>aspectRatio</strong> - Custom aspect ratio (width/height). Default is 2 (2:1 ratio)</li>
                <li><strong>resizeDelay</strong> - Delay in milliseconds before resize update (default: 0). Useful for performance optimization</li>
                <li><strong>chartwidth/chartheight</strong> - Used as max-width and initial dimensions</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-highlight" style="margin-top: 10px; background: ##fff3cd; border-left-color: ##ffc107;">
            <strong>Best Practices:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Use responsive="true" for most charts to ensure they work on all screen sizes</li>
                <li>Set appropriate aspectRatio values: 2 (wide), 1 (square), 0.5 (tall)</li>
                <li>Use maintainAspectRatio="false" when you need charts to fill specific container heights</li>
                <li>Add resizeDelay="100" or higher for better performance when charts frequently resize</li>
                <li>Combine with CSS max-width for better control over maximum chart size</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <a href="index.bxm" class="back-link">‚Üê Back to Test Suite</a>

</body>
</html>
</html>
